FBIS4-36166 "drnes109_j_94019" FBIS-NES-94-109 Daily Report 5 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Lahij Governor Vows To Implement Projects Lahij Governor Vows To Implement Projects JN0506073794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0430 GMT 5 Jun 94 JN0506073794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Lahij Governor brother 'Awad 'Abdallah Ba Matraf yesterday received the brother residents of al-Hutah, who expressed their happiness and jubilation with this meeting and welcomed the brother governor. They noted the service projects required by their city after normalcy has been restored, and after they have been rid of the iron fist, and domination of the criminal secessionist gangs once and for all. They reiterated their support for constitutional legitimacy, as well as their willingness to defend Yemeni unity, and cooperate with the governorate officials to implement the necessary projects in their governorate. For his part, the brother governor affirmed that the state will strive to address the impact of the incidents caused by the secessionist and separatist elements. He added that the state is eager to implement all necessary and urgent projects. He noted that the governorate will witness the implementation of additional projects in the coming phase. The brother Lahij governor visited several areas in the governorate, inquired about the well-being of the residents, and was briefed on the requirements and needs of the areas he visited.
